Image to Video API  
The Image to Video API enables users to create videos from image prompts. By providing an image URL and additional parameters, users can generate videos with customizable settings such as duration, aspect ratio, and optional watermarks. This service is ideal for developers looking to integrate video generation capabilities into their applications.

To authenticate with the Image to Video API, you need to use the HTTP Authorization header with the Bearer scheme. This requires an API key, which you must include in your requests. Ensure that you replace `YOUR_API_KEY` with your actual API key in the Authorization header. For more details on obtaining an API key, please refer to the service's documentation.

Relevant Links:  
- [Image to Video API Documentation](#)  
- [API Key Generation Instructions](#)
